{"name": "pystemmer", "metadata": {"name": "PyStemmer", "version": "2.2.0.3", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: Danish", "Natural Language :: Dutch", "Natural Language :: English", "Natural Language :: Finnish", "Natural Language :: French", "Natural Language :: German", "Natural Language :: Italian", "Natural Language :: Norwegian", "Natural Language :: Portuguese", "Natural Language :: Russian", "Natural Language :: Spanish", "Natural Language :: Swedish", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: C", "Programming Language :: Other", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Database", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP :: Indexing/Search", "Topic :: Text Processing :: Indexing", "Topic :: Text Processing :: Linguistic"], "home_page": "https://github.com/snowballstem/pystemmer/", "license": "MIT, BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Snowball stemming algorithms, for information retrieval", "upload_time": 1728520585}, "documentation": ["Stemming algorithms\n\nPyStemmer provides access to efficient algorithms for calculating a\n\"stemmed\" form of a word.  This is a form with most of the common\nmorphological endings removed; hopefully representing a common\nlinguistic base form.  This is most useful in building search engines\nand information retrieval software; for example, a search with stemming\nenabled should be able to find a document containing \"cycling\" given the\nquery \"cycles\".\n\nPyStemmer provides algorithms for several (mainly European) languages,\nby wrapping the libstemmer library from the Snowball project in a Python\nmodule.\n\nIt also provides access to the classic Porter stemming algorithm for\nEnglish: although this has been superseded by an improved algorithm, the\noriginal algorithm may be of interest to information retrieval\nresearchers wishing to reproduce results of earlier experiments.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "runtests", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "runtests.py3k", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "benchmark", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python", "This script runs a simple benchmark of the python stemmer interface."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "benchmark.datafiles", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "benchmark.words_lst", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "benchmark.words", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "benchmark.setup", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "benchmark.t", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "benchmark.times", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tarballfetcher", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tarballfetcher.download_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tarballfetcher.extract_tarball", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tarball_filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tarballfetcher.sha256_file", "asynchronous": false, "params":